stylometry: RISKSIMTABLE allows you to run several simulations at the same time, one for each value of some variable.  It also enables you to run several outputs at the same time based on different order quantities to figure out how much to order.  In a simulation model, you would determine your order quantities then put your risksimtable in and run the simulation.  After you run the simulation you should get a report to see what order quantity you would want to choose.  For example with the Walton problem we did in class we wanted to figure out the order quantity that would give us the largest average profit.  In doing so we listed the order quantites, then set the risksimtable.  After that we ran the simulation and we set the iritations to 5 becasue we wanted to look at 5 different order quantities and figure out which one would give us the largest mean profit and the lowest standard deviation.
